Mr. R. was a touchy, unpleasant, and rude correspondent. Hugh's dealings with him across the ocean – Mr. R. lived mostly in Switzerland or France – lacked the hearty glow of the Flankard ordeal; but Mr. R., though perhaps not a master of the very first rank, was at least a true artist who fought on his own ground with his own weapons for 